Project RollUp — future agent context

What was built
- News aggregation site with CRT-green styling and a bottom-right globe widget.
- Headline cards show title, source, timestamp, source count, inferred location, summary, and score.
- Clicking a headline opens a fact-based write-up modal.
- The globe infers location from structured metadata first, then headline/summary/body text, with confidence scoring and safe fallback.
- The backend extracts feed excerpts and article page text when possible and caps summaries at 400 words.
- The site guarantees at least 100 distinct headlines by expanding the time window, using backup feeds, and then falling back to older clearly labeled items.

